\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 23. O. tornensis} Jáv., {\i Ann. Hist.-Nat. Mus. Hung.} {\b 4}: 431 (1906). Perennial with several erect flowering stems; stems 15-30 cm, usually simple, stellate-setose. Lower leaves 30-60 × 3-5 mm, linear-spathulate, stellate-setose, above with setae 1-2 mm and rays 0·2-0·4 mm, beneath with setae 0-1 mm and rays 0·2-0·4 mm. Pedicels 0-2 mm; bracts shorter than calyx. Calyx 6-10 mm in flower, up to 12 mm in fruit, with simple and stellate setae. Corolla 14-17 mm, pale yellow, sparsely to densely puberulent, about twice as long as calyx. Nutlets 2·5-3 mm, smooth, shining. 2n = 14. •{\i  S.E. Czechoslovakia, just extending to N.E. Hungary.} Cz Hu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   Possibly not specifically distinct from {\b 22}.
